# prom-label-proxy

Enforces namespace-level label filtering for multi-tenant query isolation.

- **Upstream**: [prometheus-community/prom-label-proxy](https://github.com/prometheus-community/prom-label-proxy)
- **Downstream**: [openshift/prom-label-proxy](https://github.com/openshift/prom-label-proxy)
- **Deployed as**: Sidecar/proxy in Thanos Querier and Alertmanager

## How It Works

1. Non-admin user submits a PromQL query
2. prom-label-proxy checks user's namespace access (via SubjectAccessReview)
3. Injects `namespace=` label matcher into the query
4. Forwards the filtered query to Thanos Querier / Alertmanager

Prevents users from querying metrics from namespaces they don't have RBAC access to.

## Investigation

If users report "no data" for namespaces they should have access to, check:
1. User's RBAC bindings in the target namespace
2. prom-label-proxy logs in the Thanos Querier pod
